<span class=pageheading>5 Common First-Time Homebuyer Mistakes</span>
<br><br>

<ol style='margin-top:0in' start=1 type=1>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'>They
     don’t ask enough questions of their lender and miss out on the best deal.</li>
<br><br>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'>They
     don’t act quickly enough to make a decision and someone else buys the
     house.</li>
<br><br>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'>They
     don’t find the right real estate professional who is willing to help you
     through the homebuying process.</li>
<br><br>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'>They
     don’t do enough to make their offer look good to a seller.</li>
<br><br>
 <li class="text" style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'>They
     don’t think about resale <i>before</i> they buy. The average first-time
     buyer only stays in a home for four years.</li>
</ol>
